Risk rewards the people willing to tolerate it. That means some investors always crave risk; the harder it is to find, the more dear it becomes and the more people want it. The price of risk determines how capital is allocated; risky startups get the capital they need because they offer investors higher expected returns. The process is not always perfect, because investors might not be able to access certain markets or misconstrue information. But market-set asset prices convey more information than any alternative.
